The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Lake Davis had a population of 72. The population density was {{convert|13.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lake Davis was 65 (90.3%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (1.4%) [[African Americans|African American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (2.8%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 0 (0.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 4 (5.6%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 3 persons (4.2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Lake Davis CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0639483 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 36 households, out of which 2 (5.6%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 15 (41.7%) were married-couple households, 2 (5.6%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 17 (47.2%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 2 (5.6%) had a male householder with no partner present. 18 households (50.0%) were one person, and 14 (38.9%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.0.<ref name=DP1/> There were 15 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (41.7% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Lake Davis CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0639483 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 4 people (5.6%) under the age of 18, 6 people (8.3%) aged 18 to 24, 7 people (9.7%) aged 25 to 44, 32 people (44.4%) aged 45 to 64, and 23 people (31.9%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 58.5{{nbsp}}years. There were 25 males and 47 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 146 housing units at an average density of {{convert|26.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 36 (24.7%) were occupied. Of these, 20 (55.6%) were owner-occupied, and 16 (44.4%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] Lake Davis had a population of 45. The population density was 8.4 people per square mile (3.2/km{{sup|2}}). The racial makeup of Lake Davis was 45 (100.0%) White, 0 (0.0%) African American, 0 (0.0%) Native American, 0 (0.0%) Asian, 0 (0.0%) Pacific Islander, 0 (0.0%) from other races, and 0 (0.0%) from two or more races.  Hispanic or Latino of any race were 2 people (4.4%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0639483|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715030409/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0639483|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Lake Davis CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households, no one lived in non-institutionalized group quarters and no one was institutionalized.

There were 23 households, 2 (8.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 17 (73.9%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 0 (0%) had a female householder with no husband present, 0 (0%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 1 (4.3%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 5 households (21.7%) were one person and 3 (13.0%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 1.96.  There were 17 families (73.9% of households); the average family size was 2.24.

The age distribution was 4 people (8.9%) under the age of 18, 0 people (0%) aged 18 to 24, 5 people (11.1%) aged 25 to 44, 24 people (53.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 12 people (26.7%) who were 65 or older.  The median age was 60.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 104.5 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 115.8 males.

There were 155 housing units at an average density of 28.8 per square mile, of the occupied units 23 (100%) were owner-occupied and 0 (0%) were rented. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0%; the rental vacancy rate was 0%.  45 people (100% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 0 people (0%) lived in rental housing units.

